Converts a configuration object into a dict that matches the standard YAML
config schema.

N.B. the output of this method is ignored by the web service's API; the field
     is deprecated since Aug 2024.

Example structure partial:
{
    ...
    "display_name": "My Endpoint",
    ...
    "executor": {
        ...
        "provider": {
            ...
            "type": "LocalProvider"
            ...
        }
        ...
    }
}

Gets a dictionary that contains information about all locally
known endpoints.

"status" can be one of:
    ["Initialized", "Running", "Disconnected", "Stopped"]

Example output:
{
    "default": {
         "status": "Running",
         "id": "123abcde-a393-4456-8de5-123456789abc"
    },
    "my_test_ep": {
         "status": "Disconnected",
         "id": "xxxxxxxx-xxxx-1234-abcd-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
    }
}

